Pt was referred to ES by her step mother. In September 2012 she began to hear voices. Prior to that she was experiencing insomnia since August of that year. She took no agents for sleep. She had been smoking marijuana since July 2012. She was smoking blunts about 3x per week. <br>She also experienced paranoid delusions and reference delusions. She had paranoid ideation in that she felt threated by others. <br>"I got wierded out and got undressed outside so I was arrested for indecent exposure for a month." She was released September 5th. She had not smoked MJ after getting out but the voices were sitll occuring daily.

Since she came to ES and was placed on Latuda her voices reduced substantially. Currently she experiences AH mostly at night before bedtime.They say annoying things. "I still avoid the mirror". They say random things, but not threatening. <br>She is currently sleeping 8hrs per night. She reports anxiety "like somebody is following me but it's not as bad as before."

Prior to coming to ES she went to Midwest Medical Center in OK for a week. That was an inpatient psych unit. There they put her on Benadryl and Risperdal but "it didn't do much for me".   When she came to ES her former psychiatrist raised her Risperdal dose with improvement. Then she was switched to Invega, and pt continued to complain of AH and paranoid ideation.

Pt reports that she had never smoked marijuana before until July 2012. then she was smoking two blunts three times a week for two months before her psychotic symptoms began.  One day she was so psychotic that she stripped naked and went prancing around the neighborhood. She was arrested and spent one month in jail for indecent exposure. She has not smoked MJ since that time but the hallucinations and delusions have persisted.
Pt denies any hx of medical illness or surguries.
